Key Methods of the Optional Class
ofNullable(value): Creates an Optional that can contain a value or be empty if the value is null.
isPresent():
orElse(value): Returns the value if present; otherwise, returns a default value.
map(Function): Applies a function to the value if present and returns a new Optional.
flatMap(Function): Similar to map, but avoids nesting of Optional.

map()	flatMap()
One-to-One	One-to-Many
Returns Stream<T>	Returns flattened Stream<T>
No nesting	Removes nesting

map() transforms each element, while flatMap() transforms and flattens nested structures into a single stream.



